# panic on $app.save for settings · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #7082
created: 2025-08-10, last updated: 2025-08-17, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/7082)

The database, app settings, etc. are initialized and can be safely accessed only after app bootstrapping, aka.
you need to move your calls AFTER the `e.next()` call.
For example:
```
onBootstrap((e) => {
e.next();
const settings = $app.settings();
settings.meta.appName = $os.getenv("APP_NAME");
$app.save(settings);
});
```
With that said, note that the above is most likely wrong because you are going to overwrite with each app start the settings that may have been updated while the application has been started.
If the above needs to be executed only once, then it is better to be moved in a migration - https://pocketbase.io/docs/js-migrations/#initialize-default-application-settings
